setData.questionDescription: Can you spend 2 minutes explaing to me what JavaScript is
setData.questionAnswer: It is the scripting language of the web that was initially intended to run on the browser. Today, JavaScript is used in the server.

setData.questionDescription: In a sentance, 'have you seen the latest ECMAScript changes?'
setData.questionAnswer: It is a standard specification for scripting languages. JavaScript is based on ECMAScript.

setData.questionTitle: What is the difference between == and ===?
setData.questionDescription: It is the scripting language of the web that was initially intended to run on the browser. Today, JavaScript is used in the server.
setData.questionAnswer: == compares values. === compares both type and value.
